wn, VA, where he became a successful merchant and landholder. His son was sheriff and a member of the VA Council, and his grandson, Thomas Nelson (1738–89), a signer of the Declaration of Independence, was governor of VA."],"variants":[{"name":"Nell","meanings":["Dutch and German: from the personal name <i>Nel</i>, a shortened form of   Cornelius  .","South German: nickname from Middle High German <i>nelle</i> ‘crown of the head’, perhaps denoting an obstinate person.","English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Nelle</i>. This may sometimes have been a variant of <i>Nele</i> (<i>Nigellus</i>, see   Neal  ), but it was probably more often a pet form of the commoner name <i>Elias</i> (see   Ellis  ) with a prosthetic <i>N-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Toothaker","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of Swiss German <b>Totenacher</b>, a habitational name (recorded in Konstanz in the 14th century) for someone from Todtnacht in Thurgau, Switzerland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Toothaker Nelson was born in 1525, in Riccall, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Rodger Toothaker 1st."},"et":{"1525–":"1525–Surnud","1523–Male":"1523–Surnud","1550–Male":"1550–Surnud","1525–Female":"1525–Surnud","1525":"1525","1523":"1523","1550":"1550","Riccall, Yorkshire, England":"Riccall, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, London, England":"London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1525–":"1525–Kuollut","1523–Male":"1523–Kuollut","1550–Male":"1550–Kuollut","1525–Female":"1525–Kuollut","1525":"1525","1523":"1523","1550":"1550","Riccall, Yorkshire, England":"Riccall, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","London, London, England":"London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1525–":"1525–Décédée","1523–Male":"1523–Décédé","1550–Male":"1550–Décédé","1525–Female":"1525–Décédée","1525":"1525","1523":"1523","1550":"1550","Riccall, Yorkshire, England":"Riccal